  ("npc1_personalityclash_speech", "I feel disgusted having to share a party with {s11}. He acts so superior yet has spent his entire life in the service of others, never his own man. "),
  ("npc2_personalityclash_speech", "You do yourself dishonour having {s11} in our company. He is a Skaven, a plague on this world, and he is a ruthless killer with no ounce of goodness in him."),
  ("npc3_personalityclash_speech", "{reg33?Madame:Sir}, I appeal to you to relieve {s11} from your service as he is a threat to my life and to others here who he dislikes. You cannot control him or keep him in line, it is only a matter of time."),
  ("npc4_personalityclash_speech", "{reg33?Madame:Sir}, you need to do something about the evil barbarism of {s11}. He tries everything he can to stop me from saving the life and health of your troops and he makes threats to me I fear he will carry out."),
  ("npc5_personalityclash_speech", "I couldn't care less that {s11} hates me, but not being able to kill him is driving me insane. I will honour the mercenary code as you pay well but at least send him away, preferably to a task he can't possibly survive."),
  ("npc6_personalityclash_speech", "{s11} may be virtuous but he is a poor judge of character. He continually insults my character but he knows nothing of my world or the work I do."),
  ("npc7_personalityclash_speech", "I had heard of this {s11} character before I joined your party. Most people have and his reputation is certainly formidable but after spending some time with him I am left quite underwhelmed."),
  ("npc8_personalityclash_speech", "Do you know how much money {s11} makes. He even takes a tithe from his venators just for using his name, and they call me a thief."),
  ("npc9_personalityclash_speech", "Is hiring {s11} some kind of joke. You can be questionable as a leader at the best of times but you look like a fool having him in your employment."),
  ("npc10_personalityclash_speech", "If some of our troops are close to death then let them die. There is honour in death, {s11} dishonours the Gods by doing his healing and surgery."),
  ("npc11_personalityclash_speech", "When I leave I will pay you a handsome sum if you release {s11} as well. I will have my troops ready to take him back to the black towers for torture and eventual death."),
  ("npc12_personalityclash_speech", "Booooooooooooooooooooooooooo {s11}, Bug wants to slice and dice."),
  ("npc13_personalityclash_speech", "{reg33?Madame:Sir}, I understand that not everyone aspires to the same code as me but there is a limit to what I will tolerate and {s11} is that limit."),
  ("npc14_personalityclash_speech", "Captain I am most upset with {s11} being in our group. I have only just got over the great evil he committed against me and now seeing his face every day is bringing it all back."),
  ("npc15_personalityclash_speech", "The reason I have respect for all cultures and races is that behind the rituals, beliefs and psychological particulars there are many similarities between us all and at our base we are not so different. There is alot to admire in most races and individuals."),
  ("npc16_personalityclash_speech", "I know that I am not as effective on the battlefield as others here but I feel that any criticisms should come from you and not {s11} as you are my leader."),
  ("npc17_personalityclash_speech", "{playername} I object to that drunken dwarf {s11} being in this crew with us. He never does anything anyone tells him, I have even seen him ignore some of your orders recently. He is a law unto himself."),
  ("npc18_personalityclash_speech", "I must admit it is fun winding up Florin but at the same time he is a pathetic pain in the arse. Men have this complex where they have to be thought of highly and they have to be better than there peers, especially women."),
  ("npc19_personalityclash_speech", "For a race so territorial it is funny how they always encroach upon our territories in the Amazon. They are hypocrites and {s11} is the biggest one of them all."),
  ("npc20_personalityclash_speech", "When I said I would join you I didn't think I would have to spend any time with {s11}. She is a liar and a cheat and she owes me a lot of money."),
  ("npc21_personalityclash_speech", "Excuse me Captain but can I ask that {s11} be formally dismissed. He has offended me greatly as well as being an all round untrustworthy companion."),
  ("npc22_personalityclash_speech", "Captain I have my respect for the skills of the fighting women of Amazonia but not for {s11}. She is lightweight and also incredibly ignorant"),
  ("npc23_personalityclash_speech", "You know Captain that {s11} is not a very good sport. I mean her no harm in my compliments, it's just when a fine single lady is in my presence why would I not turn on the Bastich charm."),
  ("npc24_personalityclash_speech", "I know that I am not as effective on the battlefield as others but I feel that any criticisms should come from you and not {s11} as you are my leader."),
  ("npc25_personalityclash_speech", "One moment Captain. I know strength and power are extremely useful for an ambitious leader such as yourself but intelligence is also an important attribute and I fear that {s11} is far too lacking in that area."),
  ("npc26_personalityclash_speech", "Why Thrud get more respect than me? Everyone speaks of him like he is a God yet no one sees that I am the best fighter in your party."),
  ("npc27_personalityclash_speech", "You are supposed to destroy the undead not have them fight with us, especially their best troops."),
  ("npc28_personalityclash_speech", "The chaos have been invading the Empire for generations at the cost of tens of thousands of lives. They are dirty fighters and relentless and I have hated them since I was a young boy."),
  ("npc29_personalityclash_speech", "I just don't like that {s11}."),
