  ("npc1_personalityclash2_speech", "Why by Grungi's beard is {s11} in our company. We are not a charity, this is serious business."),
  ("npc2_personalityclash2_speech", "{reg33?Madame:Sir}. I don't like the intentions of our companion Eketi. His mission is to give the Dark Elves total dominance of the seas but this would be a very bad thing."),
  ("npc3_personalityclash2_speech", "{reg33?Madame:Sir}. Sometimes in life we all make mistakes, none of us are flawless I am sure you will agree. Admittedly I caused great upset to Maephilin by killing one of his horses but I am truely sorry, I really am but he will not let it go, not even for a day."),
  ("npc4_personalityclash2_speech", "{reg33?Madame:Sir}. If there is one thing which I have done it is surely shown my trustworthiness and that I am genuine. Most in our party can see this but {s11} just will not accept it."),
  ("npc5_personalityclash2_speech", "I have always found the tongues of Elves irritating, but listening to Maephilin singing all day long is making me want to slit my own throat. The Elvish language sounds sophisticated but really they are just saying the same stuff we all say in an overly pretentious way."),
  ("npc6_personalityclash2_speech", "My lord. It enrages me to have {s11} in our company. I wouldn't even need to be here if it wasn't for him. We had the Witch Elves on the run and virtually beaten. I sent out a fleet to cut them off at the ocean and when we arrived on the beach I expected them all to be dead."),
  ("npc7_personalityclash2_speech", "{playername} you must do something about {s11} at once! Skill is a talent needed on the battlefield but so is discipline and he has none."),
  ("npc8_personalityclash2_speech", "You know I love goats cheese and I will go to any lengths to get the best. Unfortunately the best means I have to get near that nasty piece of vermin Skeezle."),
  ("npc9_personalityclash2_speech", "Of all the cuddly virtues ever created by this planets inhabitants honour and chivalry have to be the worst."),
  ("npc10_personalityclash2_speech", "{s11} seems very proud that no would be assassin has managed to get past him while he has been a personal bodyguard. I can tell you now that I would have no problem getting past him."),
  ("npc11_personalityclash2_speech", "I have always considered humans as a low rank of species but none are lower than Felix Jaegar. He thinks that because he reads and can use his language expressively that he knows more than you or I and that his opinions matter more as well."),
  ("npc12_personalityclash2_speech", "Hack slash, bash bash bash. Stupid Braganza"),
  ("npc13_personalityclash2_speech", "{reg33?Madame:Sir}, if you are going to have big personalities in this army then you could find some more amiable than {s11}. He says he achieves nothing but good and that the end result is all that counts but how one conducts oneself matters also."),
  ("npc14_personalityclash2_speech", "Captain. {s11} is making me incredibly nervous in battle. I was dehorsed in that last battle and he looked at me with such a menacing face, like I was the enemy."),
  ("npc15_personalityclash2_speech", "Throughout my studies I have got a good nose on who to trust and who not to trust. It may seem unusual as many seem to like him but I don't trust Oggy. Orcs are not like other races, they have one of the most primitive minds and are not programmed for intuition and creativity."),
  ("npc16_personalityclash2_speech", "I an finding {s11} an insufferable companion. I don't have much to look forward to in life but at least I have my cheese or at least had some cheese, {s11} stole it."),
  ("npc17_personalityclash2_speech", "{playername} that is the 5th time now I have asked {s11} to cover my back in battle and she has run off looking only out for herself. I have had more than enough trouble from her over the years and the last thing I want is to be cut down because she will not work as a team."),
  ("npc18_personalityclash2_speech", "Don't you ever want to just give {s11} a slap captain, or maybe just shake him out of his dull serious existence. A lizardman's smile is hardly endearing but it wouldn't hurt to crack one every now and again."),
  ("npc19_personalityclash2_speech", "I can't stand that {s11}, he is always coming onto me and trying to fawn over me with his stinking stupid self. He is always drunk and while he is harmless he is getting too much for me."),
  ("npc20_personalityclash2_speech", "How much longer is {s11} going to be travelling with us? He will not be quiet about my weekly wage and the debt I owe him."),
  ("npc21_personalityclash2_speech", "That Elf {s11} is a fine warrior but he is far too serious if you know what I mean. Even after the tragedies that have befallen me I know how to be merry and how to cut good folk some slack from time to time."),
  ("npc22_personalityclash2_speech", "You need to be careful who you trust captain. That {s11} will betray you the second she sees the glint of gold in her eye."),
  ("npc23_personalityclash2_speech", "I know I am not as quick of body or mind as I used to be but I am an elder and God damn I deserve to be respected. BELCH!"),
  ("npc24_personalityclash2_speech", "I normally would not trouble you with complaints of others but I feel it is getting dangerous to have {s11} in the party with us."),
  ("npc25_personalityclash2_speech", "Of all the foul things which Nagash did, the birth of the tomb Kings had to be the worst of them, They were resting peacefully until he laid a curse upon the land and awoke one of the most powerful factions in the world."),
  ("npc26_personalityclash2_speech", "Everyone thinks that Ogres are so dumb and that humans are smart but they are not so smart, especially the chaos. They can be as stupid as a troll."),
  ("npc27_personalityclash2_speech", "I have killed more Ogres in the last 2 years than humans Uggluk has killed in his entire life. He is a weak fighter who cannot even beat the laziest tyrant in existence."),
  ("npc28_personalityclash2_speech", "Must you have someone quite as brutal as Thrud in our party? His brain is full off 100% violence and nothing else. He is as thick as an Ent's trunk and has no redeeming qualities."),
