  ("npc1_personalityclash2_speech_b", "Don't be fooled into thinking he is a competent warrior just because of his equipment. He will always be the pathetic little rodent I knew when he was younger. He is nothing but a burden to those around him and that includes you. Just be rid of him."),
  ("npc2_personalityclash2_speech_b", "They are evil and have no respect for anyone but their own kin who they see as vastly superior to all. The only faction they are willing to keep pacts and promises with is Skaven and that says enough in itself. If he is successful the world will turn into a frightful place."),
  ("npc3_personalityclash2_speech_b", "You see I was on high alert protecting my employer and Maephilin came charging down the path with his bow in hand. I tried to fire a warning shot across the front of the horse but I misjudged it's speed. I had never seen a horse this fast so I was not aware my shot was possibly a danger but it speared through the horses head and killed it. I have apologised 1000 times but now I am frustrated, please tell him to let it go or leave."),
  ("npc4_personalityclash2_speech_b", "He keeps watching me, like he is observing my behaviour and when I asked him why he said he was waiting for me to show my true colours. When he is sharpening his arrows he always gives me glances, it makes me nervous. He is an intelligent man too and others respect him for that. I am worried that others will start to believe his theories about me."),
  ("npc5_personalityclash2_speech_b", "Queekish is short, sharp and to the point. Words are often pointless anyway. He says he is going to sing of his favourite place in the world tomorrow, I swear once I am done here I will go and release a pestilence there and leave it to rot and decay."),
  ("npc6_personalityclash2_speech_b", "What we didn't count on was Eketi bringing in the entire Dark Elf fleet, annihilating our own, killing most of men on the beaches and escorting the Witch Elves to the new world. Now he aims to make them stronger, which means if we fail now we may never get another chance."),
  ("npc7_personalityclash2_speech_b", "He doesn't listen to orders and has no style to speak of. He doesn't know the meaning of the words stealth or halt and you cannot depend on him for anything. With such ill discipline he is a hinderance rather than a help to your cause."),
  ("npc8_personalityclash2_speech_b", "He stinks, his stuff stinks and touch the wrong thing and you can catch some festering plague we have not even heard of in the moot. Plus he is an insufferable character in himself, he would be better off out of the party, especially now I have all his cheese and there is no use for him."),
  ("npc9_personalityclash2_speech_b", "You can see by his beam how proud Sir Aristide is of his virtuous life. The man is a joke, you only get half of what you need to do done when you live by such rules. Find an enemy and destroy them, by any means, that is the easiest and most definitive way."),
  ("npc10_personalityclash2_speech_b", "I would kill him and all the other bodyguards first and then walk past his lifeless corpse to claim the skull of his master. No need for stealth or cunning, just take them all out. I would take extra pleasure in killing him as I hate the cowards who are so proud of their ranged weapon skills. A real warrior fights toe to toe."),
  ("npc11_personalityclash2_speech_b", "He hates us as well as the Skaven. Hate isn't a bad thing but he doesn't know how to use it. He isn't even that good a fighter, he isn't much good at anything that isn't self indulgent. He is more pathetic than superior."),
  ("npc12_personalityclash2_speech_b", "He will kill me when I awake but maybe when he sleeps? Bug scared, needs more medicine."),
  ("npc13_personalityclash2_speech_b", "I have heard stories of him leaving people to die, destroying cultural artefacts and using dishonesty and manipulation to achieve his goals. Yes he may have prevented evil from prevailing but at what cost? At the cost of honour and what makes us a blessed race."),
  ("npc14_personalityclash2_speech_b", "I thought for a minute he was going to jump at me but he seemed to restrain himself. I have never given him any reason to feel ill at me, in fact we have barely spoken. Please have a word with him."),
  ("npc15_personalityclash2_speech_b", "His love for medicine is unusual, too unusual for an Orc and I fear there is something wrong with his brain. It may be damaged or under some kind of spell and if that is the case then he could switch at any minute and do something unpredictable, maybe even dangerous. I have seen Orcs with brain problems suffer fits of psychosis and there are always deaths. He may seem normal but trust me Orcs should not act like this."),
  ("npc16_personalityclash2_speech_b", "It was the best goats cheese you can eat and nowhere we are visiting has anything close for sale and most of the good shops won't even sell it to me. Why is my life so depressing."),
  ("npc17_personalityclash2_speech_b", "She has a talent for tracking and she does it stealthily for a human but over the years she seemed to think our forests welcome her when they do not. She was always trying to sneak in and whilst she can elude some of our rangers she cannot elude me. 3 times she has been in prison yet she still illegally returns to our forests. I suggest you get in someone more trustworthy."),
  ("npc18_personalityclash2_speech_b", "Oh the injustice, oh the troubles my kin face, that is all you hear from him. You would think that the Lizardmen were the only race in the world to have problems. He needs to get laid but that might risk a {s11} offspring which doesn't bear to think about."),
  ("npc19_personalityclash2_speech_b", "I fell over in that last battle and he could see I was ok yet he ran over to give me the kiss of life. It was so unnecessary and I can still taste it now."),
  ("npc20_personalityclash2_speech_b", "I know I owe him money but I owe others money too and I intend to pay them off first. Some of the characters I am in debt to are a lot more concerning than Joseph Bugman if you know what I mean. He will get his money he just has to wait, will you help me get that through to him?"),
  ("npc21_personalityclash2_speech_b", "{s11} is probably the most unwelcoming souls you could meet. There is a reason he is often on his own when we camp yet many flock to sit with me. For every bit of morale his crack shot arrows give us, his hostile demeanour takes right away."),
  ("npc22_personalityclash2_speech_b", "I know you pay her well but for {s11} no amount is enough. She will always go after the bigger prize no matter where her loyalties should lie."),
  ("npc23_personalityclash2_speech_b", "{s11} is too concerned about what I am doing and not enough about what she is doing. Better whip her up into shape Captain, quick smart."),
  ("npc24_personalityclash2_speech_b", "The problem is that, to be frank.... well it's the smell. He stinks and he gives away our position from a mile off. One day he will attract the wrong kind of beast at us and we will be done for."),
  ("npc25_personalityclash2_speech_b", "They are a plague upon the world and they are hated by all which is why I advise you to release {s11} from your company. He is no good for army morale."),
  ("npc26_personalityclash2_speech_b", "Erasmus is the stupidest of them all. He think he can train me to be better and that some of my fighting style is wrong or energy inefficient as he puts it whatever that means. He can teach me nothing, I am a killer and I could crush him to prove it."),
  ("npc27_personalityclash2_speech_b", "I get the feeling he wants to fight me, if he challenges me to a duel I will take his head off of his shoulders. You can take compensation from my wages."),
  ("npc28_personalityclash2_speech_b", "I understand you need great fighters but there are others out there like Gotrek or Sir Aristide who will think before they shed blood. That is just as key a talent as Thrud's kill now, leave the consequences to everybody else."),
  ("npc29_personalityclash2_speech_b", "I can't stand watching them fight."),
