  ("npc1_personalitymatch_speech", "Another fine victory, the wetter my axe the better. It am glad to see the manling {s11} fighting by my side again as well."),
  ("npc2_personalitymatch_speech", "{reg33?Madame:Sir}. I am indebted to you for bring {s11} along with us on our quests. I am bound to him by an unbreakable oath and while he is here I am fulfilling both my duty to him and to you."),
  ("npc3_personalitymatch_speech", "Hello, {reg33?madame:sir}! I had just wanted to tell you that {s11} is a wonderful companion to have with us. If there is one thing I admire it is focus and he has it in abundance."),
  ("npc4_personalitymatch_speech", "A toast to your victory {reg33?madame:sir}. We looked determined out there, especially {s11}. It may seem weird that someone as soft as I favours a killer as cold as {s11} but I owe him a lot."),
  ("npc5_personalitymatch_speech", "An efficient skirmish master. Our enemies were quick to fall to the floor. {s11}'s healing skills have also helped us recently, as distasteful as his lack of fighting skill is we need as many troops battle ready as possible to fulfil our missions."),
  ("npc6_personalitymatch_speech", "You have done me a good deed by taking {s11} into our company. I admire men who live a life of protecting others. From a very early age he decided to dedicating his life to protecting those who are vital to his country."),
  ("npc7_personalitymatch_speech", "Although he has never got much respect from others I must admit that I have a level of admiration for {s11}."),
  ("npc8_personalitymatch_speech", "A fine battle that was {playername}. And I have to say, I admire watching {s11} leading the charge in battle, he is truly amazing."),
  ("npc9_personalitymatch_speech", "Battles are fun when you fight next to {s11}. He is totally insane! He just goes and does his thing, there is no real method or goal, just hack hack hack."),
  ("npc10_personalitymatch_speech", "I normally like remain solitary when we camp but I must admit that I enjoy talking to {s11}. He is a great fighter with big plans of his own."),
  ("npc11_personalitymatch_speech", "If you want to go far in this world captain then you have to know how to handle yourself. All Dark Elves are taught how to fight from birth. We have skill and we have emotion and we know to use them. The same can be said for {s11}."),
  ("npc12_personalitymatch_speech", "Bug like {s11}."),
  ("npc13_personalitymatch_speech", "It is a good thing we have {s11} with us in our group. War can be a depressing thing, that goes without saying. There is always so much at stake that it is hard to know how to raise a smile."),
  ("npc14_personalitymatch_speech", "Captain. It is a pleasure travelling with men like {s11} by my side."),
  ("npc15_personalitymatch_speech", "I don't get as much time to talk to you as I would like {reg33?Madame:Sir} but I enjoy talking to Maephilin as we have a lot in common."),
  ("npc16_personalitymatch_speech", "Most of my idols are Skaven but I have a lot of admiration for {s11} whom I have known by reputation for a long time."),
  ("npc17_personalitymatch_speech", "I am not one to look favourably on others but I find {s11} is a good companion to be around. She has done a lot in her life although not all of it is tasteful it must be said. She is charismatic and certainly knows how to whip the lazy troops up to speed."),
  ("npc18_personalitymatch_speech", "Serious people are not really my thing but I am becoming fond of {s11}. Pistols will always be my thing but I have a soft spot for archery and he is the best I have seen."),
  ("npc19_personalitymatch_speech", "You know every time I see Florin I fall in love all over again. He has the perfect face and body and he is such a courageous and noble man."),
  ("npc20_personalitymatch_speech", "Everyone loves to be loved right! and I have that with {s11}. She is really in to me if you know what I mean, all it takes is a short poem or a deep gaze of my eyes and she will do whatever I want for the rest of the day."),
  ("npc21_personalitymatch_speech", "You know I love that {s11} captain. It is off characters like him that I made my fame and fortune. An absolute pisshead he is, he out drinks most dwarves I swear it."),
  ("npc22_personalitymatch_speech", "Of all the outsiders who come to Lustria {s11} is the most welcome. She is a real traveller, an inquisitive women who admires without touching."),
  ("npc23_personalitymatch_speech", " I don't believe in the Gods captain but I believe in {s11}."),
  ("npc24_personalitymatch_speech", "I tell you what captain, we are lucky to have {s11} supporting us in the field. I am always worn out after a battle but he always looks like he has just got going."),
  ("npc25_personalitymatch_speech", "If there is one warrior who would not benefit from my training it is {s11}, he is already a one man killing machine."),
  ("npc26_personalitymatch_speech", "I used to work for Lord Albertus when I was younger and he was a daring adventurer and explorer. He was never fond of the duties which came with being an Empire Lord and just wanted to be, well more like Florin as sad as that sounds."),
  ("npc27_personalitymatch_speech", " Erasmus is a good friend to me. I used to train in his pit fighting clubs many years ago. He would also take me on tour to pit fighting tournaments where we would both win lots of money off of my victories."),
  ("npc28_personalitymatch_speech", "They say that Ogres make untrustworthy companions but I have never found it so, especially not Uggluk. I used to lead a party not too different from your own and Uggluk was my best warrior."),
  ("npc29_personalitymatch_speech", "Boss. {s11} back there didn't do badly in that last fight at all. Their a good egg, too."),
