  ("npc1_personalitymatch_speech_b", "We are like brothers and although I have saved him from a tight spot many times, he has done me good to. I cannot think of anyone I would rather have write my life story."),
  ("npc2_personalitymatch_speech_b", "When I first started my journeys with Gotrek I thought my time with him would be short. One who looks for death usually finds it quickly in this world. It seems that Gotrek even defies the Gods and while the seemingly never ending nature of my oath can be frustrating, it is exciting to be living the story of one of the greatest slayers ever to have lived."),
  ("npc3_personalitymatch_speech_b", "Whether we are talking about on the battlefield or a wider tactical plan he sees everything through with the utmost precision. I am surprised I hadn't heard of him before he came here to be honest."),
  ("npc4_personalitymatch_speech_b", "He saved my life a few years back while I was trekking through the mountains. I was captured by an angry Dwarf who was going to do all manner of things to me. Ripnitch jumped out of nowhere to attack him and after he saved me he even asked me to tend his wounds so he didn't die. Maybe he isn't so heartless after all?"),
  ("npc5_personalitymatch_speech_b", "He helped me out one time near Karak a Karak. I was hired to capture a prestigious Dwarf runesmith and when I caught up to him he had {s11} as a prisoner. I attacked him but I am trained too well and he was greatly wounded. I was about to kill Oggy as well but I saw he had a medical book in his possession so I asked him to see to the Dwarf. Whatever he did worked as the Dwarf survived and my mission was saved."),
  ("npc6_personalitymatch_speech_b", "Even though many will say otherwise I have also dedicated my life to protecting my kin from the evil that walks this world. It is often a thankless task but when you love your country you don't need recognition to know how important you are."),
  ("npc7_personalitymatch_speech_b", "He has worked to improve himself at all costs his whole life and that is an admirable thing. He was always laughed at and mocked when he was weak but he persevered and can hold his own. He will never be mighty but not everyone can be, for his level he has done extremely well."),
  ("npc8_personalitymatch_speech_b", "I don't usually get star struck. I don't care much for the so called legends of the Old World but I must admit Sir Aristide is one I cannot help but admire. Powerful on the battlefield, graceful in manner and authoritative in presence. I have not even stolen anything in his presence so as not to disrespect his virtues and believe me that is a first."),
  ("npc9_personalitymatch_speech_b", "He is a dreamer and you can rarely understand a thing he says. I would love to know what he thinks about all day."),
  ("npc10_personalitymatch_speech_b", "One day he will lead many tens of thousands of Elves to establish dominance of the sea. I will enjoy watching him slaughter his way to power almost as much as I will enjoy taking it off him when after I go home and call forth the great Northern fleet."),
  ("npc11_personalitymatch_speech_b", "It is a shame he is not a Dark Elf because I know Malekith would love to have him do his bidding. He is frightening to watch on the battlefield and I would stand no chance against him."),
  ("npc12_personalitymatch_speech_b", "Bug like you too."),
  ("npc13_personalitymatch_speech_b", "{s11} is a surprising source of positivity. He is always in a good mood and looking to make things easier for others in any way he can. He always respects things he doesn't understand which can't be said about many others. He may not be much of a fighter but some companions can be crucial in other ways."),
  ("npc14_personalitymatch_speech_b", "He is such a learned and intelligent man. I thought I knew a lot about the world but he is knowledge far surpasses mine. He takes such care and attention in examining detail he finds and is very careful in forming his opinions. If you ever need advice about how to deal with other races, I would recommend asking him."),
  ("npc15_personalitymatch_speech_b", "He has travelled a lot just like me and also has a vast knowledge of many things. His views are a bit biased but that is to be expected. He has a knack for song which I envy greatly as well as a voice to match. Musical talent is something Elves have over other races I must admit"),
  ("npc16_personalitymatch_speech_b", "Skaven armies are experienced underground or in the field but we are yet to really master the art of sieges like other races have. If our leaders had his knowledge and mind for siege warfare we could change the face of the earth."),
  ("npc17_personalitymatch_speech_b", "She is a bit of an adventurer and a treasure seeker which is the kind I normally hate but she is a sea faring lady and always will be so she will never be a threat to my kingdom as we are far inland. The pirates, just like us, often have to face tough odds to survive and I respect that."),
  ("npc18_personalitymatch_speech_b", "There isn't a better feeling than blowing the head off of an assailing Skaven but sometimes I miss the speed and grace a bow and arrow seems to have. I saw him claim a head shot before the enemy had a chance to move in the last battle."),
  ("npc19_personalitymatch_speech_b", "He always promises me we will be together but he always heads off on adventures but that is his profession so I understand. One day I will marry him though, I am sure of it."),
  ("npc20_personalitymatch_speech_b", "Don't get me wrong I do like her and she is beautiful but ultimately my dream girl needs to be a bit more worldy and battle wise. It is nice to have someone to share the nights with though I won't deny it."),
  ("npc21_personalitymatch_speech_b", "I test my limited edition brews on him all the time. The promise of a few barrels is enough for him to test any formulas for side effects and whatnot. Some weird things have happened to him but he has never complained and I have always got the recipes spot on after his input."),
  ("npc22_personalitymatch_speech_b", "She is very stealthy too. Sometimes we do not know she is in Lustria for a few days after she has arrived. She is very knowledgeable and respectful and she has dined with Reverend Itzatecah on a few occasions such is her standing. You see lizardmen are not aggressive to all outsiders, just the ones who come to fill their pockets."),
  ("npc23_personalitymatch_speech_b", "His brew is as heavenly and as great a gift as was ever given by a living soul to another. All my pay goes on it you know."),
  ("npc24_personalitymatch_speech_b", "We have been friends for years and I have seen him lead his troops into battle and win against incredible odds. He protects his country intensely just like Scarloc but he does so because others like to come and steal their sacred treasures. That is a valid reason but no one tries to take anything from the Wood Elves yet Scarloc acts in the same way. He is a disgrace compared to {s11}."),
  ("npc25_personalitymatch_speech_b", "He is powerful, direct and absolutely fearless. Tactics, deception and subtlety are not his strong points but they don;t need to be when you can do what he can do. You made a good decision signing him up."),
  ("npc26_personalitymatch_speech_b", "He always treated his troops well and always showed me great respect by giving me the best cuts of meat every meal. It is a shame what happened to him, now there is no meat on him at all."),
  ("npc27_personalitymatch_speech_b", "I have never fought with him in battle before until now and he still has style for an old man."),
  ("npc28_personalitymatch_speech_b", "We fought the Lizardmen who are extremely tough to fight but he was always the one who got us through the tight battles. So long as you keep him well fed he will be nothing but an asset."),
  ("npc29_personalitymatch_speech_b", "We get along really well."),
