  ("npc1_home_description", "I always hear warriors claim to have fought the best, I imagine you believe some of your fights have been historic. But let me tell you now that until you have gone toe to toe with a Bloodthirster you will not know what it is like to fight true power."),
  ("npc2_home_description", "The Empire likes to be pioneers when it comes to technology but when it comes to laws we often get it all wrong. The Emporer had put in place a window tax, can you belive it? charging a citizen just to view these beautiful lands from our own houses. I was outraged and whipped up a sterling protest to which the official response was to send in troops."),
  ("npc3_home_description", "The weather is always stable here however so I had to leave my home. If you want to learn to fire an arrow accurately at range in high winds then Copher is not the place to do it. I spent alot of the times in the mountains as the weather there is atrocious and I learnt much practicing in that climate. I came back as the best shot in the city."),
  ("npc4_home_description", "I learnt to speak Riekspiel from merchants while I was very young. While my tribe was either squabbling with each other or preparing to give Bonerencha camp another bashing I used to sneak into the Imperial Lands, sometimes as far as Talabheim and try to find some literature. It is there I found books on anatomy and physiology and what surprised me more than my desire to read it was how well I understood it."),
  ("npc5_home_description", "Seer Kruekel had called all available assassins in for a special assignment. Only one assassin was to get the job and it was given to one with not even half the skill I possess. The target was was an Orc warboss in Karak Vlag who, according to our spies, was trying to persuade Garbalu to expand into Skaven territory. An easy target which should have been given to me in the first place."),
  ("npc6_home_description", "We nearly won the first time. We took the Witch Elves completely by surprise in one of their outdoor rituals. Most of their population was there and we descended on them with all the anger in our hearts and will in our minds. There was so much smoke from our firearms you could have seen it from the Empire."),
  ("npc7_home_description", "Look at all the merchant Princes now, all disposed by the pirates. It won't be long before they are destroyed as well. The best thing you can be in Tilea is an elite mercenary, you can have riches and position in society without fear of being plotted against. I am seen as a resource in the game of power, nothing more."),
  ("npc8_home_description", "It used to be a base for the skaven in the dark early days, who knows what remains down there but one day I plan to find out."),
  ("npc9_home_description", "What they did not realise is that we fight just as well drunk or hungover as we do when sober and nothing gets us more riled and determined than being pitted against units of Imperial or Bretonnian knights."),
  ("npc10_home_description", "It was not until I took some of my men into the northern lands of the Empire that I realised that we had been holding ourselves back from a source of even greater bloodshed and pillage. Our lands are small compared to the rest of the World, we must take our armies south and slaughter all in our path."),
  ("npc11_home_description", "Lord Fellheart has chosen me for a very important mission before the big campaign. I have to learn all the secret pirate coves and lairs so we know where to hit hardest. I have already learnt a lot whilst travelling with you. Our invasion will be victorious and absolute."),
  ("npc12_home_description", "To be honest I cannot remember much of my past, it is all a blur."),
  ("npc13_home_description", "Couronne is my City as well. I won many tournaments in Couronne's arena, the most prestigious tournaments around and run by the King himself. I impressed him with my fighting skill and good graces and he awarded me the title 'master of the tournaments', a title of which I am both humbled and honoured."),
  ("npc14_home_description", "The fields and hills in that part of Ulthuan are the finest to learn the mastery of horses. We breed some of the fastest horses ever seen and I have been riding them since I was very young. I believe that horses are closer to the Gods than any other animal."),
  ("npc15_home_description", "It is normally a very safe place apart from occasional raid by the Tomb Kings which can leave this defensively weak part of our kingdom in ruins. I respect all the kingdoms in this land apart from the Tomb Kings who I hate with a passion. Words cannot express my feelings towards them."),
  ("npc16_home_description", "It is a requirement to be tough with the Stronghold being on the border of what was the Wood Elf lands. Anyone who shows weakness is ridiculed and I was the worse of them."),
  ("npc17_home_description", "My kin have lived there for a long time and we have a special bond with forests. There are many who believe we are too territorial but when you see the desecration that befalls other lands in times of conflict you will understand why we are so desperate to keep our forests free of any potential threats."),
  ("npc18_home_description", "Luckily for me the ship was owned by one of the most fearsome captains of his time and he raised me up by himself and taught me everything I need to know about how to survive in this world."),
  ("npc19_home_description", "I was just going for a walk and he was looking for a magic stone. We sat and talked for hours, he told me of his adventures and all the courageous things he has done in his life. He is the perfect man don't you think?"),
  ("npc20_home_description", "My mother hid me in a caravan during the red pox outbreak caused by Clan Eshin which destroyed the population. There was a quarantine and no unauthorised personnel were allowed in or out of the castle. My mother was resourceful though and she smuggled me away. She died along with the rest of my family but I always give thanks to her for saving my life."),
  ("npc21_home_description", "There are many secrets in this world {playername} and the recipe to my XXXXXX is one of them. I created the recipe after years and years of study and toil and the result is the most popular brew in all of history."),
  ("npc22_home_description", "After we destroyed the great Chaos threat in the south we thought we had earned the respect of the whole world but to our horror we were then the ones being invaded."),
  ("npc23_home_description", "On second thoughts you don't have time for that captain, another time maybe. I am from here though, I used to sell goods on the road from the stuff my brother would take from the Elven ships."),
  ("npc24_home_description", "I am suspicious of what the guild does but I keep my mouth shut. My cousin says it wants to share technology with the new world in exchange for resources but I fear we will take but give nothing back."),
  ("npc25_home_description", "My father taught me how to use every kind of hand held weapon. He died while I was young but not before I had learnt enough to be able to hold my own and protect my family against the Empire. I stayed and fought until I heard about the pit fights in Mordheim and the money and respect that comes from being victorious there."),
  ("npc26_home_description", "A chaos army will not care about your cause but it will fight against your enemies like they are fighting for Archaon himself. The tyrant who rules my kingdom is gluttonous and has failed to uphold our status in relation to the other tribes."),
  ("npc27_home_description", "They taught me to fight and then sent me to the greatest fighting school to master my trade. When I was 5 I got expelled for killing 27 pupils and 3 teachers so I ran into the wilderness and taught myself everything else I needed to learn."),
  ("npc28_home_description", "When I returned I proved without a shadow of a doubt that I am who I say I am but they chose not to listen. Even men I would call my brothers denied me even though I could see in their eyes that they knew."),
  ("npc29_home_description", "Being here makes me feel nostalgic."),
