  ("npc1_home_description_2", "I have slain these beasts, I have slain whatever Khorne, Tzeentch, Slaanesh and Nurgle have thrown at me. I wonder if there is a foe out there capable of taking my life or if I will end up dying of old age. I would go after Nagash if I knew where he is but he has not been seen or heard of in decades."),
  ("npc2_home_description_2", "It was probably foolish of me but I charged the troops head on and Gotrek, who admires such stupidity, dived in to save me despite not knowing me at all. We celebrated his victory, as it wasn't really mine, at the Screaming Cat tavern. In a drunken stupor I vowed to follow him around until he is slain and then write about his life. It is a seemingly neverending quest and I fear that whatever kills Gotrek will make short work of me, the books may never be written after all."),
  ("npc3_home_description_2", "I couldn't have come a moment to soon though as political turmoil meant many prominent figures were getting killed. I stepped up to help and in a way it stole my childhood but I had a responsibility and I wouldn't be the man I am today if I stood by and did nothing."),
  ("npc4_home_description_2", "My tribe always used to call me manlike much to my shame and when they found out how much alike I was hounded out my village. Word spread around the kingdom and soon there was no Orc that did not know and ridicule me for my passions. I thought getting a job as an apothecary for the Gouged Eye team would earn me some respect but it only made things worse. Orcs just have no concern for the powers of healing."),
  ("npc5_home_description_2", "I followed the assassin and as he crept through Sleekit I took my chance and went for him. We fought briefly on the bridge but I was too fast for him. I cast his body down the river and personally undertook his mission to kill the warboss. News came through of my success to Kruekel and he rewarded me with more work. Being on Kruekel's personal killteam is a good position to start your career in, now I am here with you which will be equally prosperous."),
  ("npc6_home_description_2", "Those that survived fled for Hag Graef but little did they know that we had besieged half the city and had an army outside the gates. They then fled for the coast as we predicted but Eketi thwarted what we thought was the final act."),
  ("npc7_home_description_2", "I should not be too critical of those who aspire for power as they are my potential employers and the last 8 years have been very lucrative for me. There are wars everywhere."),
  ("npc8_home_description_2", "Sadly with the Saurus paranoia at its most neurotic it can be really hard to get this far into Lustria without being marched out again or worse. I will try and get my hands on a good map showing the least beaten paths and use those."),
  ("npc9_home_description_2", "We spotted their ambush and charged them head causing many casualties in the first hit. The battle was scattered and disorganised from there but we had the best of it and forced a retreat of the Imperial army back to Averheim. Hahahaha, I will never let them forget it."),
  ("npc10_home_description_2", "I took my army all the way down to the border princes and into the badlands before we were finally forced back. The next time we tried the Empire was more prepared but we love a challenge and the war continues."),
  ("npc11_home_description_2", "Once we have control of the seas we would have effectively split the world in two which will make it much easier to move towards widespread conquest."),
  ("npc12_home_description_2", "All I know is that I discovered mad cap and that was that. Speaking of which where is my stash.............."),
  ("npc13_home_description_2", "I fought side by side with the King in the Battle of Swamphold, a last stand against the mighty Orc invasion and arguably the Kings finest hour. Since that battle he has trusted me with his life, he trusts me above all others, and he trusts me now to fulfill my duty and bring back the blessed banner and secure our nations safety forever."),
  ("npc14_home_description_2", "I never wanted to be a warrior, I wanted to breed horses but the Dark Elf threat mobilised the entire island 50 years ago and I decided to join the Reavers but that did not work out because you need to be great with a lance as well as a bow. I am a mighty fine horse archer though as I am sure you can see."),
  ("npc15_home_description_2", "They are pure evil with no positive features about them. They are a kingdom of merciless expansionists who have no care for the beliefs and rights of other kingdoms. There only desire is to destroy, to kill as many inhabitants of this world as they can. They want everyone dead, just like them.'"),
  ("npc16_home_description_2", "My life was hard but in times of intense war I was glad to be on the mountains. There is much Clan Moulder and many rat ogres on Foul Peak and the Wood Elves would often leave us alone and head for Mordheim. I am glad there are no Wood Elves here anymore."),
  ("npc17_home_description_2", "The rumours that no one is ever allowed in are unfounded, you for example would be welcome in our lands. We are however stricter than other kingdoms and we do it for good reason. It is not just us that wishes our land to be so protected but the forest itself wills us to be vigilante. You can hear her wailing when she is at unease, the recent disaster is the great tragedy of our time."),
  ("npc18_home_description_2", "Most men don't realise, they just see a pretty face or think I am in fancy dress but they soon find out. My father told me everything about male anatomy, it was very enlightening, hahaha."),
  ("npc19_home_description_2", "I hear stories from others about him doing some pretty cunning and dishonest things but they must be mistaken. My Florin is a paragon of virtue, and a great kisser."),
  ("npc20_home_description_2", "Growing up without a family is hard but not unusual considering the world we live in. I travelled the world and learnt much whilst in my teenage years, I took whatever I could from each culture to better my ability to provide for myself in any circumstance. You may not think it but I am a wily old fox at the best of times, I just get in over my head every now and again."),
  ("npc21_home_description_2", "Being a brewer is more than just my passion, it is my duty. Many dwarf armies have been galvanised by a night on my brew on the eve before battle. It is an important part of dwarf culture, which is why the whole kingdom rallied in anger to the goblin raid which caused such devastation to my home."),
  ("npc22_home_description_2", "The Tileans were the worst of them all, they gained the most from our victories. We gave them their land back from the Chaos yet they came here to expand their territory. It is unforgivable."),
  ("npc23_home_description_2", "It was a good living but it got dangerous and my wife was driving me mad with her incessant nagging whenever I got home. I got a chance to join a prestigious ship one day and left by the back door."),
  ("npc24_home_description_2", "Most of the nations in that part of the world don't want us there or our knowledge. We should leave but more traders and their mercenaries turn up every day."),
  ("npc25_home_description_2", "Since I joined I only ever lost twice, once to an ogre and another time to a Black Orc Big Boss. I made full recoveries and since then I am unbeaten. Once I had retired from fighting I stayed on as head trainer at Thanquol's request. He wanted Mordheim to train the best fighters to keep more money running in than at other cities. That is what I did {playername}, Mordheim pit fighters are the fiercest in the world."),
  ("npc26_home_description_2", "Our tribe was held in high esteem in the days of my father, now the others call us 'tanfuksham gajum' which means 'almighty sleep' in orcish, because our tyrant is lazy and has us do nothing. I wish to change things back to the way things were and reclaim our status among the tribes. It will be a tough mission as despite his lethargy our tyrant beat me before, and beat me well. I will be better prepared this time."),
  ("npc27_home_description_2", "Since then I have had killed over 10,000 enemies, or so they say, I am not good with numbers."),
  ("npc28_home_description_2", "Since then they have all laid claim to my land and my riches. I have lost everything, material, social and spiritual. If my loyalty to the Emperor was not so strong I would have a good mind to raise an army and take it all back."),
