  ("npc88_kingsupport_3", "With your permission I shall go spread word of your right to be {reg33?Queen:King}."),
  ("npc1_kingsupport_objection", "Are you a clown {playername}? I know you want to be {reg33?Queen:King} but maybe you should consider the jesters hat instead of a crown. First you send off skeezle in your own name and now you are considering him to be your head bodyguard. You are a joke and so it he."),
  ("npc2_kingsupport_objection", "If you want to be taken seriously then sending a Skaven to champion your claim is the worst thing you could do. I really don't understand your decision, Skaven are scum, is that how you want to be seen?"),
  ("npc3_kingsupport_objection", "Beorg's policy of destroy and conquer is a great evil you should not associate yourself with. You are no tyrant, do not be swayed by the ways of chaos."),
  ("npc4_kingsupport_objection", "Captain, every ruler in the land will see you sending Beorg out as emissary as a threat to their land. The only reason you send a cold blooded killer to speak for you is if you want to send a warning, there is nothing diplomatic about it. I fear a grave response."),
  ("npc5_kingsupport_objection", "Do not ally yourself with the underdogs as soon as you become {reg33?Queen:King}. The Wood Elves will soon be a thing of the past, skaven on the other hand will grow from strength to strength. There is a better alliance for you."),
  ("npc6_kingsupport_objection", "Are you out of your mind appeasing the Dark Elves over their naval plans. Do you have any idea what the fate of the world would be if they controlled the seas? It will be a perfect set up for their domination of all the land. You must see sense."),
  ("npc7_kingsupport_objection", "What are you trying to achieve by sending Gotrek out as a political envoy? If you need a champion in a duel then he is your warrior but in the subtle game if diplomacy he is a naive choice."),
  ("npc8_kingsupport_objection", "{reg33?Queen:King} I would call Eleanor back if I were you. She is a con artist and is well known for it. If she goes around calling herself your trusted companion everyone will think you are a cheat too."),
  ("npc9_kingsupport_objection", "If you want to make an impression upon those who hold power then don't send Felix as your envoy. He bores me to tears and I can tell you that I am not the only one who he has that effect on. If you want to be King you need to make an impression, and sending Mr all talk and no fight is not the right one to make."),
  ("npc10_kingsupport_objection", "You want people to think you a weak {reg33?Queen:King}? Then why send the weak Sir Aristide. Soft rulers perish in this land, I should know, I have slain enough of them."),
  ("npc11_kingsupport_objection", "A ruler who cares for all classes always takes their eyes off the ball. Soft policies like the one Abdul is suggesting will lead to your downfall, concentrate on the strong classes of your society, the ones which will further your power and the power of your realm. The others can look after themselves."),
  ("npc12_kingsupport_objection", "Boo Abdul."),
  ("npc13_kingsupport_objection", "I have a good mind to leave your service right now. To send Beorg for such an important role, when honourable gentleman such as myself are associated with you and are tarnished by this infamous play. It is infamous!"),
  ("npc14_kingsupport_objection", "Captain if you have the skaven running your security and intelligence agencies you will be viewed with suspicion by everyone. Every time there is a murder or a plot unhatched somewhere your country will always get the blame and this will lead to war. Do not indulge Ripnitch in his ambitions."),
  ("npc15_kingsupport_objection", "{reg33?Queen:King} if you want people to legitimise your claim then you need to send out people who are articulate, well spoken and with a knowledge of foreign relations and the customs of this world. Bastich is the polar opposite of this, I fear you have made a great mistake and your reputation will suffer for it."),
  ("npc16_kingsupport_objection", "You know Volands is the bastard son of the Emperor right? By sending him out as your diplomat you will alarm all those in the Emperors circle who know. They will think you plan to replace Karl Franz and they will seek to destroy you. The Empire is too big an enemy to make for a new kingdom."),
  ("npc17_kingsupport_objection", "I see Bugman has wormed his way in to your inner circle. Acting as your diplomat, no doubt earning your trust so he can get ahead with his businesses in your new kingdom. It is up to you if you want to trust him but if you want important diplomatic work done it is best he is nowhere near it, or any dwarf for that matter."),
  ("npc18_kingsupport_objection", "You can make Florin feel like a big man without having him do such an important job for you. He will mess this up as he always does you can be sure of it and you will be the one to suffer, He just wants an ego boost that comes with being someone important, he does not care about your claom."),
  ("npc19_kingsupport_objection", "I am so glad you have sent Bastich away but I am sorry you sent him on such an important mission. I really want you to become {King\Queen} but he will make you a laughing stock. Find out where he went and steer clear of there in future."),
  ("npc20_kingsupport_objection", "Dark Elves are treacherous {playername}, everyone knows this. You send out Eketi to speak well of you but you don't know what he will say when he gets there. He could well spread discontent to increase your enemies and start a war once your kingdom is formed. This could act as a distraction for the Dark Elves to make their move."),
  ("npc21_kingsupport_objection", "Skeezle is a lowlife {playername}, having him as your personal bodyguard would be like me choosing Jalil or Abdul Khaliq as my master brewers, what the hell would they know about making ale! If you need a personal bodyguard just choose Thrud or Gotrek if you can promise him the right amount of danger."),
  ("npc22_kingsupport_objection", "The less land the pirates have the better. An island will just be used as a base for more of their illegal raiding and plundering of the south coast. Even with you as her {King\Queen Eleanor should not be trusted."),
  ("npc23_kingsupport_objection", "Amazons are heathens {reg33?Queen:King} and while she is a pretty heathen she is a heathen never the less and having her supporting your claim will only raise suspicion about your own beliefs. Best call her back."),
  ("npc24_kingsupport_objection", "You should have told Bastich to stay sober when you agreed to have him go out garnering support for your claim. Heaven knows what he will say when he is out there, he is notorious for saying the wrong thing after a few hours on the rum."),
  ("npc25_kingsupport_objection", "A mild manner, orc healer is a bit of a novelty and if you don't mind me saying using him as a diplomat sends out the wrong message if you want to be seen as a real player among the ruling families in this world. You should have sent someone with authority and a hint of menace like Volands or Gotrek."),
  ("npc26_kingsupport_objection", "Bug is dumb and you are dumb for thinking he can help gain you any support for your claim. What is he going to say that makes any sense to people, nothing! What good is that? His place is on the battlefield and that is it."),
  ("npc27_kingsupport_objection", "Sir Aristide is all words and no action. For all his chivalry I have killed more enemies and saved more lives than he could dream of. You should send real heroes out to champion your claim and not posers like him."),
  ("npc28_kingsupport_objection", "Volands is a maverick and a man lacking in manners. He has a warrant for his death in 2 countries and he is wanted for arrest in 3 others. Sending him out to gain you support for your claim will only weaken it. The amount of noble families he knows who will listen to him are very few."),
  ("npc29_kingsupport_objection", "I don't support your decision to send them off to spread support."),
