  ("npc1_fief_acceptance", "I don't know what use you think I would have for a fief such as {s17}. Nevertheless you are trying to be generous so I will accept your offer and figure out what to do with it later."),
  ("npc2_fief_acceptance", "My family will be very proud to see me as the Lord of {s17}. I have not always been the son they wanted and I know I have displeased in the past but this will surely make them see what I am worth. Thank you so much."),
  ("npc3_fief_acceptance", "{reg33?My Lady:Sir}, it is most generous of you to offer me {s17}. I would be pleased to hold it, and dedicate myself to the spiritual and physical uplift of its inhabitants."),
  ("npc4_fief_acceptance", "It is a great surprise that you would grant me {s17} as a fief. I am not respected by most yet you would do me this great honour. Thank you."),
  ("npc5_fief_acceptance", "I would be most pleased to hold {s17}. I will send word to my brothers that I have a safe and protected place to bury victims and items that are best never found, for a price of course."),
  ("npc6_fief_acceptance", "{playername} I have little time to rule but know some trusted administrators who can keep things running in my stead. You do me more than just honour by giving me this fief, I now have a base for my campaigns and a place to host council meetings. I am in your debt."),
  ("npc7_fief_acceptance", "I am reluctant to accept {s17} as it makes me more of a target as I was before. However I will not be in this position forever and when I retire I will need a place of my own so I will accept your generous offer."),
  ("npc8_fief_acceptance", "Thank you {reg33?Madame:Sir}, this is a most unexpected honour. It is usually impossible for Halflings to gain foreign land anywhere other than the Empire. This will raise my status back at the moot, it will justify everything I have ever done."),
  ("npc9_fief_acceptance", "This is why I knew you would be a good employer. You remember those who have contributed most to your success. I accept this honour and will hold a 3 day drinking festival in your honour."),
  ("npc10_fief_acceptance", "You amuse me with this offer. I usually take what I want rather than be given but you are not of pure mind so it is to be expected. I am fulfilled in your army so I will accept your offer rather than undermine you in front of your troops."),
  ("npc11_fief_acceptance", "You are very smart {playername}, giving land to the commander of the Naggaroth fleet will completely throw your enemies. They won't know what to think and will be second guessing your intentions as well as your political strength. This is always an advantage."),
  ("npc12_fief_acceptance", "Skreeeeech you are good to me. I would give you some madcap to say thank you but I have taken it all, hahahahaha."),
  ("npc13_fief_acceptance", "I was born to hold land and to watch over communities of gentle folk but I did not think I would hold land in any other country other than Bretonnia. You do me great honour by deeming me worthy of this position. I accept most graciously."),
  ("npc14_fief_acceptance", "You do me a great honor, captain. In Ulthuan, a youngest son such as myself has few opportunities to earn a fief of his own. But in other kingdoms there is still the chance for a warrior to win with with his spear, the privilege which is so hard to earn under Finubar. I shall hold {s17} as your vassal, and raise an army to fight for your glory and for your kingdom."),
  ("npc15_fief_acceptance", "Well, {reg33?my lady:sir}, that's a gracious act, and marks you as the kind of monarch who can save this sorry land from the incompetence of the current batch. I suspect a lot of the noble lords around here will think that a commoner like me isn't fit to hold a fief. Well, when they see what I do with it, and what revenues I can bring in, they'll change their tune!"),
  ("npc16_fief_acceptance", "Oh, that's most generous of you, {reg33?my lady:sire}. I've been in and out of many a great hall or manor -- not always with the owner's permission, I should add -- but I never thought I'd own one myself."),
  ("npc17_fief_acceptance", "To accept a new home when my people have none seems like a crass, dishonourable thing to do but we need a sanctuary for our injured, one nearer civilization as our new location does not provide for us in the same way Laurelorn does."),
  ("npc18_fief_acceptance", "You are a friend indeed {playername} and a mighty fine leader if you don't mind me saying so. I am now the lady of my own domain, this calls for a new hat."),
  ("npc19_fief_acceptance", "You are too generous {reg33?Madame:Sir}, now I have a family home where I can bring up some children with Florin. I wish he would stay with me and stops going off on his adventures. He always says soon but there is always a reason for him to go."),
  ("npc20_fief_acceptance", "I am not normally one who would wish to be anyone's vassal but for a fief of this quality I don't see how I can say no. Show me to my new land."),
  ("npc21_fief_acceptance", "You know I have my own fief back home but I have left my friend in control until I am ready to return. It is a great responsibility to have so many people under your protection and I failed my duty when the goblins took so many of their lives. Maybe if I treat the people of {s17} well then I can regain my honour and think about going home."),
  ("npc22_fief_acceptance", "We have been seeking for a place on foreign soil to set up a base for our intelligence agency and {s17} is perfect for this. I am grateful for this and the honour you have shown me by granting me this title."),
  ("npc23_fief_acceptance", "I was always wondering where I would stay when I retire but now you have provided me with the perfect spot. You have my thanks Captain, lets have a drink to celebrate."),
  ("npc24_fief_acceptance", "I am honoured and humbled by your generosity and you can be sure I will treat my subjects with the utmost care and respect. Just give me one year and you will see how things will flourish around here."),
  ("npc25_fief_acceptance", "The fief of {s17} is a quality piece of land and one I will use it to maximum effect. It will train fine soldiers and hopefully grow enough food for the entire army. In a world of war we must be prepared."),
  ("npc26_fief_acceptance", "Thank you {playername} I owe you one. I will take it's ownership to my new kingdom when I claim my throne but I am sure you knew that anyway."),
  ("npc27_fief_acceptance", "Thrud is confused by the gift but will take it. Anyway where is the next battle?"),
  ("npc28_fief_acceptance", "Oh {playername} you are a loyal friend and leader. I did not think I would ever own my own land again but you have changed my destiny. You can count on me to make this a stronghold of defence for your realm."),
  ("npc29_fief_acceptance", "It would be my honor to serve you by governing {s17} for you."),
