  ("npc1_turn_against", "I set out to fight the most powerful foes and all I found was you. I will sever your head from your body and then go and look for a real challenge."),
  ("npc2_turn_against", "This is a sad day. I never thought that I might meet my old leader on the field of battle. Even if I triumph, it will bring me no joy."),
  ("npc3_turn_against", "Oh {playername} -- what a tragic turn our lives have taken! I can only hope that the tides of war that have made us enemies, will one day allow us to be friends."),
  ("npc4_turn_against", "By York and Mork.... I'm not sure what to say. If we must fight, let's get it over with."),
  ("npc5_turn_against", "{playername}, you are better suited to open battle and troop leadership than I but I have seen how you work and I may yet end the day with a hefty ransom from your treasury. To arms! ."),
  ("npc6_turn_against", "It angers me more than anything I can say to meet you like this, {playername}. I shall not dwell on the circumstances that have led us to this point. I can only say that I trusted you and my faith was not rewarded."),
  ("npc7_turn_against", "Too many times I have met a previous employer in combat, do not think anything of it. It is just business."),
  ("npc8_turn_against", "I will see you on the battlefield, watch your pockets chum."),
  ("npc9_turn_against", "I salute your strength and your courage. Once I have defeated you and taken the spoils, the world will once again tell tales of mine."),
  ("npc10_turn_against", "I expect you to be one of my toughest opponents and then I expect you to die. Face me in single combat if you dare, I will be looking for you."),
  ("npc11_turn_against", "As successful as you are you now face an opponent who knows your style and your troops! Neither will lead you to victory today. If I take you prisoner I will not have you taken back to Naggaroth which as I am sure you know is a considerable kindness."),
  ("npc12_turn_against", "Boo."),
  ("npc13_turn_against", "It is sad to meet you as my enemy  -- but on the other hand you have disgraced yourself and justice deserves to see me take you away in chains. That I ever followed you was my failing but I can start to make amends now. To arms."),
  ("npc14_turn_against", "Well, {playername}. We meet as enemies. I confess that I have mixed feelings. It grieves me to make war on you, but if we meet in battle and I prevail, I will have defeated one of the greatest commanders in the world, and I will know that my mastery of the military art is complete!"),
  ("npc15_turn_against", "Ah... I have not been looking forward to this day. I just want to say that in my sight, if you'd kept your faith in me, things would never have come to this. But no doubt you see it differently."),
  ("npc16_turn_against", "Hello, Captain! So, I guess we're enemies! I am sure you are not in the slightest bit worried but you don't know how skilful I am. Yes! If I defeat you then no one can say anything again. Prepare to DIIIIEEEE!!!"),
  ("npc17_turn_against", "It seems you have ended up an enemy, just like all the rest. It makes me lose hope that even you turn down the same selfish, honourable path as all the others. Let's finish this quickly."),
  ("npc18_turn_against", "Don't bother challenging me to a duel, I would rather just shoot you right between the eyes. Haha, look out for me on the battlefield, I will be the one with my sights bearing down upon you."),
  ("npc19_turn_against", "Florin save me!."),
  ("npc20_turn_against", "It looks like fate has set us against each other. You are the more skilled I give you that but my troops will fight to the end for me and we are fresh for the fight unlike your battle worn shower."),
  ("npc21_turn_against", "So many enemies I have made recently and now you too have added your name to the list of those who will feel my wrath. To think I once respected you."),
  ("npc22_turn_against", "As always the tides have turned and war must be fought amongst those that were once comrades in arms. You have my respect as a commander and you will have my respect as a prisoner once you are defeated ."),
  ("npc23_turn_against", "This will end badly but what the hell, I am too old for this anyway."),
  ("npc24_turn_against", "I am wordly enough to know fear and I know you well enough to fear you in open battle. Nevertheless my duty to my soldiers is to maintain their honour and that means we must take up arms against you."),
  ("npc25_turn_against", "So we meet on the battlefield {playername}. I have seen your methods and have always been impressed but you have not seen all of mine, a wise fighter never reveals all to his employer. These troops of mine though have had the benefit of my full training and they are more than ready for you."),
  ("npc26_turn_against", "Before I become tyrant there is one thing left for me to do. Rip your head and spine from your body and make a nice club with it. I will use it to pound my foes to mush."),
  ("npc27_turn_against", "I will break you."),
  ("npc28_turn_against", "From friends to enemies, it is a story I know all too well. This story doesn't end well for you {playername}, I will no longer stand idle against such treachery. Your head on a spike will send out the right message."),
  ("npc29_turn_against", "Wha! I thought you were someone I could rely on {playername}."),
